<i>When our descendants ask us
in the future what our generation</i>

00:58.270 --> 01:03.000
<i>bad done for them and
what we had achieved for our country,</i>

01:03.600 --> 01:08.140
<i>let us proudly answer them,
without any hesitation that we labored</i>

01:08.140 --> 01:11.630
<i>again and again with faith
in the modernization of our country.</i>

02:13.910 --> 02:18.210
Man... what the fuck.
He's not picking up?

02:18.310 --> 02:19.510
Nope.

02:21.920 --> 02:25.040
That fucking bastard.
He's pulling out.

02:25.250 --> 02:26.380
What do we do?

02:26.490 --> 02:29.460
What else can we do?
We should break in.

02:34.730 --> 02:36.720
But the door's locked.

02:37.260 --> 02:38.530
Shit.

02:40.200 --> 02:44.190
- Hey, you have the key?
- How would I have the key?

02:45.710 --> 02:49.300
- OK. Try calling him again.
- Alright...

02:50.610 --> 02:52.910
The fucker must be
inside there somewhere!

02:57.890 --> 02:59.080
Is it locked?

03:01.190 --> 03:03.680
Sir.
Don't get anything from here.

03:03.960 --> 03:07.260
The owner's a greedy one,
he doesn't even pay us.

03:26.410 --> 03:27.440
Hello?

03:30.750 --> 03:33.520
Hey, sorry but I don't think
I'll make it.

03:34.620 --> 03:37.750
I'm still in training.

03:42.560 --> 03:44.090
I said I can't today.

03:45.470 --> 03:47.260
My co-worker's coming.
Sorry.

03:48.440 --> 03:50.800
- Did anyone stop by?
- Nope.

03:51.270 --> 03:52.640
Thank God.

03:56.440 --> 04:01.540
The bus stopped on my way,
so I came running here.

04:02.220 --> 04:05.580
I'm not the late type,
but it's easy to be late around here.

04:12.190 --> 04:16.720
- It's okay right?
- Yeah, it's okay.

04:18.870 --> 04:20.300
You came early?

04:21.640 --> 04:23.470
No, I just came on time.

04:24.270 --> 04:25.700
Are you from around here?

04:27.170 --> 04:28.270
No.

04:29.580 --> 04:31.840
Then how did you find this work?

04:32.880 --> 04:35.440
A friend who used to work
here introduced me.

04:36.650 --> 04:39.640
Sounds good.
We don't get too many people here.

04:39.990 --> 04:41.620
There's nothing hard
about the work, really.

04:41.620 --> 04:44.490
Just get to work on time,
that's all.

04:49.730 --> 04:54.190
Hey... don't tell the boss that
I was late today. Just between us.

04:56.200 --> 04:59.230
But you're gonna quit anyways.

04:59.940 --> 05:02.910
It's always good to leave on
a clean note.

05:07.880 --> 05:10.850
Hey, can you teach me
how to balance the accounts?

05:11.150 --> 05:14.050
- I didn't teach you that already?
- Nope.

05:22.600 --> 05:24.660
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

05:26.100 --> 05:29.900
Press this button to check the prices
when you're balancing the accounts.

05:33.640 --> 05:36.130
I wish all this money were mine.

05:37.650 --> 05:41.710
- You like money?
- Who doesn't?

05:42.720 --> 05:43.840
You don't?

05:43.920 --> 05:45.220
Yeah, I do.

05:52.230 --> 05:56.720
If a customer checks out,
then you press this button to calculate.

05:57.060 --> 05:58.930
- Try it.
- Yeah.

06:04.840 --> 06:06.140
That'll be 5,000 won.

06:07.310 --> 06:09.110
- Hey.
- Yes?

06:09.580 --> 06:11.100
No.
I'm talking about you, lady.

06:12.150 --> 06:13.250
Me?

06:13.250 --> 06:14.680
Who do you think I am?

06:15.050 --> 06:17.110
Why are you using me
to explain things to him?

06:17.220 --> 06:18.910
Is this how you work?

06:20.220 --> 06:21.490
Where's the owner?

06:21.490 --> 06:23.620
- Tell him to come out!
- What?

06:23.760 --> 06:25.090
You're the owner?

06:25.990 --> 06:27.120
We're really sorry.

06:30.230 --> 06:34.960
You think getting paid's a joke?
Let's get something straight, alright?

06:35.740 --> 06:40.500
It's all about keeping it real
in this world. You got that?

06:43.280 --> 06:45.940
We're really sorry.
Good-bye.

06:48.680 --> 06:49.940
What was that about?

06:52.250 --> 06:53.520
What do you mean.

06:53.750 --> 06:56.950
<i>- What did you apologize for?
- Sorry?</i>

06:58.430 --> 07:01.160
Do you always say
sorry that easily?

07:03.500 --> 07:04.690
I'm sorry.

07:05.330 --> 07:09.270
- For what again?
- For saying sorry.

07:35.800 --> 07:40.670
Hey... I'm going out smoking.
I'll be back.

07:41.340 --> 07:42.890
Alright.

07:55.320 --> 07:56.520
<i>Why don't you pick up your phone?</i>

07:56.520 --> 07:59.750
I told you not to call again.

07:59.750 --> 08:02.280
<i>Can't we just meet
and talk over this?</i>

08:02.460 --> 08:05.120
How many times do
I have to tell you, it's over!

08:05.760 --> 08:07.730
I'm so sick of it.

08:08.360 --> 08:10.920
You, and this place...

08:11.270 --> 08:12.460
<i>Hana...</i>

08:13.800 --> 08:16.000
I should've never come here
in the first place.

08:18.610 --> 08:20.160
Don't call me ever again.

08:45.600 --> 08:46.930
Are you done yet?

08:49.340 --> 08:50.630
Look.

08:51.840 --> 08:53.140
Do you like it?

08:59.410 --> 09:01.640
<i>Hey, you look really pretty.</i>

09:01.780 --> 09:03.150
Hana, you look prettier.

09:03.280 --> 09:06.980
No really.
You're much, much prettier. Really.

09:07.290 --> 09:10.220
You're the prettiest
of all the girls I've seen.

09:17.900 --> 09:19.530
There's something on your face...

09:58.170 --> 10:02.340
Okay, okay.
Just for a little bit, okay?

11:12.310 --> 11:14.580
I didn't know you were that angry.

11:21.690 --> 11:24.050
I'm really sorry.

11:31.230 --> 11:36.970
Hey.
I'm kind of curious.

11:38.770 --> 11:41.000
Why are you so polite to me?

11:41.380 --> 11:43.500
I feel a bit uneasy.

11:45.950 --> 11:47.150
What, being with me?

11:47.150 --> 11:50.380
No, no.
Just letting my guards off.

11:50.520 --> 11:53.210
You don't feel uneasy around me?

11:53.420 --> 11:56.410
- No, you're easy to be around with.
- Me?

11:56.860 --> 12:00.350
Just talking like this, you know.

12:09.670 --> 12:11.540
I'm famished from all the crying.

12:17.640 --> 12:19.540
Do you have a girlfriend?

12:22.220 --> 12:24.280
I shouldn't like someone right now.

12:24.380 --> 12:25.250
Why not?

12:26.390 --> 12:28.080
I'm beginning
my military service soon.

12:29.390 --> 12:31.120
How much time do you have left?

12:32.260 --> 12:33.620
3 months.

12:35.830 --> 12:38.560
That's no reason
to not like somebody.

12:38.670 --> 12:40.830
Feelings don't work that way.

12:42.140 --> 12:44.330
I have to make someone
wait for me.

12:44.440 --> 12:47.740
I don't like that, you know,
being irresponsible.

12:48.110 --> 12:52.440
So you must've thought I was irresponsible
when I kept you waiting just before.

12:53.050 --> 12:55.670
21 minutes is different
from 21 months.

12:55.820 --> 12:57.880
How are those different?

12:58.320 --> 13:01.340
What do you think
you'll be doing in 21 minutes?

13:02.090 --> 13:05.290
Who knows.
Maybe here...

13:07.360 --> 13:09.190
what about after 21 months?

13:10.830 --> 13:13.200
I'm not sure.

13:13.530 --> 13:14.520
Why?

13:15.100 --> 13:20.510
Wheter it's 21 minutes or 21 months,
nobody knows what's gonna happen.

13:20.940 --> 13:24.170
- Don't you think so?
- Yeah...

13:25.850 --> 13:27.840
I think it's the same
with relationships.

13:28.220 --> 13:32.550
Nobody knows what
it'll be like in 10 years, in 1 year,

13:32.550 --> 13:36.610
or 1 minute, you know.
Don't you think?

13:38.030 --> 13:41.460
But the moment you're in love,
it all feels true,

13:41.460 --> 13:44.950
so there's no room for regret
when it ends.

13:47.330 --> 13:49.640
For me, I'm always going to begin
with a clean slate no matter

13:49.640 --> 13:51.070
how many times I break up.

13:54.140 --> 13:57.240
Another customer.
You think you can do it on your own?

13:57.380 --> 13:57.930
Yeah.

13:58.080 --> 14:00.440
Then I'll go to the storage
and get the stock list.

14:13.030 --> 14:15.050
What were you talking about
with that girl?

14:16.260 --> 14:17.860
Nothing much, really.

14:18.630 --> 14:20.030
How was the audition?

14:22.040 --> 14:24.060
'Maybe next time.'

14:24.640 --> 14:26.870
You know there's not
going to be a 'next time'...

14:29.940 --> 14:33.280
There's auditions everywhere.

14:33.450 --> 14:39.390
Nobody knows what it'll be like
in 1 year or 10 years...

14:40.590 --> 14:45.620
You'll get it some day if you start out
with a clean slate every time.

14:45.960 --> 14:47.720
I've faith in you.

14:50.560 --> 14:52.120
Thanks anyway.

14:56.400 --> 15:01.430
Hyunsoo,
did you mean what you said?

15:01.980 --> 15:03.270
What do you mean?

15:03.680 --> 15:05.700
That you'll wait for me.

15:06.050 --> 15:08.610
I can bear 21 months.
It's nothing to me.

15:11.150 --> 15:13.520
You're not meeting
with someone else, are you?

15:31.340 --> 15:32.770
Hyunsoo, I love you.

15:35.840 --> 15:38.110
I wish time could stand
still right now.

15:39.310 --> 15:43.650
Hey, don't check out other guys
while you're there.

15:43.780 --> 15:45.650
I'm trusting you on this.

15:56.530 --> 15:59.270
Excuse me,
I won 500 won on these.

15:59.270 --> 16:00.160
OK...

16:03.300 --> 16:04.100
here it is.

16:04.100 --> 16:05.200
Thank you.

16:12.810 --> 16:18.250
<i>The party you're trying to call
is not available.</i>

16:18.250 --> 16:19.910
<i>Press 1 if you'd like to
leave a voice mail.</i>

16:21.590 --> 16:22.850
Hi, Mr. Chun.

16:22.960 --> 16:25.590
I need to leave early today
for an important appointment,

16:25.590 --> 16:27.230
but the next shift isn't here yet.

16:27.230 --> 16:29.320
Could you please
give me a call when you can?

16:38.870 --> 16:40.270
<i>- Yes, Mr. Chun.
- You called me?</i>

16:40.270 --> 16:42.300
Mr. Chun, I need to leave early
for today's audition.

16:42.410 --> 16:45.580
<i>There's no one else there,
so what do you mean you need to leave.</i>

16:45.580 --> 16:46.450
But the thing is...

16:46.450 --> 16:49.550
<i>If you leave now,
you won't get your pay.</i>

16:49.550 --> 16:51.350
<i>- That's that.
- Hello? Mr. Chun?</i>

17:00.560 --> 17:02.390
- Excuse me!
- Yes?

17:02.930 --> 17:05.450
I won 1,000 won with this.

17:05.800 --> 17:07.099
Would you like it in cash?

17:07.099 --> 17:10.000
No. I'll just get 2 lottery tickets
with it, please.

17:14.710 --> 17:17.109
- Alright... here you are.
- Thank you.

17:24.280 --> 17:26.619
In Jesus' name we prayed, Amen.

17:26.619 --> 17:30.960
Our Father in heaven,
hallowed be your name...

17:30.960 --> 17:32.990
<i>- Hello?
- Where are you, Mr. Lee?</i>

17:32.990 --> 17:36.630
I'm on my way there now.
The traffic's a bit rough.

17:36.630 --> 17:38.800
<i>Your turn's coming up soon.</i>

17:38.800 --> 17:40.870
I'll be right there as soon as
I cross this light.

17:40.870 --> 17:41.960
<i>Please come here
as soon as you can.</i>

17:42.070 --> 17:46.010
I'm sorry but could you audition
other people first?

17:46.010 --> 17:48.240
<i>That's going to be difficult...</i>

17:48.240 --> 17:51.010
<i>- OK. I'll be right there.
- Please hurry up.</i>

17:53.510 --> 17:57.010
Namu amitabul gwanseum bosal...

18:02.820 --> 18:10.030
Ha, you ain't got no money?
Then fuck off.

18:10.030 --> 18:14.690
That's the rule here.
You think I don't know this town?

18:14.830 --> 18:16.860
Money rules here,

18:16.970 --> 18:20.340
so why'd I work for you
if you ain't got no money?

18:28.920 --> 18:30.350
That'll be 1,200 won.

18:33.190 --> 18:34.180
Excuse me?

18:34.290 --> 18:35.280
Excuse me!

18:36.920 --> 18:37.760
Yes?

18:37.760 --> 18:40.420
It's 1,200 won.
You gave me 1,000.

18:43.330 --> 18:44.730
I'll come back again later.

18:54.940 --> 18:59.980
Ha, you ain't got no money?
Then fuck off.

18:59.980 --> 19:04.580
That's the rule here.
You think I don't know this town?

19:05.850 --> 19:08.090
Money rules here,

19:08.090 --> 19:10.750
so why'd I work for you
if you ain't got no money?

19:11.220 --> 19:12.920
Fucking asshole.

19:14.530 --> 19:16.090
Fucking asshole...

19:22.040 --> 19:24.600
If you ain't got no money,
then fuck off.

19:25.070 --> 19:27.230
Get the fuck off!

19:29.180 --> 19:30.160
Excuse me.

19:31.040 --> 19:33.310
Again?

19:33.780 --> 19:37.310
Aren't you being a little rude?
I'm a customer, you know!

19:38.350 --> 19:41.220
I was just practicing
for my audition.

19:42.660 --> 19:44.750
So you won the lottery again?

19:45.260 --> 19:49.350
No, it's a miss.
Just give me a new one, please.

20:00.310 --> 20:01.430
Here it is.

20:22.460 --> 20:24.160
<i>- Hello?
- Are you coming, Mr. Lee?</i>

20:24.160 --> 20:26.230
Yes, I just got off the bus.
I'll be right there.

20:26.230 --> 20:29.960
<i>- Your turn is coming up very soon.
- I'm sorry. I'm almost there.</i>

20:31.710 --> 20:32.830
Shit.

20:43.080 --> 20:45.210
Excuse me,
I'll have another lottery ticket.

20:46.320 --> 20:49.720
I'm sorry, sir.
But we're all out.

20:49.820 --> 20:54.780
What? But there was
some here a while ago...

21:08.310 --> 21:11.040
Excuse me,
do you have a religion by the way?

21:11.340 --> 21:13.240
No, I don't.

21:13.610 --> 21:16.510
Then... throw these away
for me, please.

21:23.790 --> 21:25.450
- Hello there, sonny.
- Oh, hi.

21:25.630 --> 21:27.650
- Lee Hyeon-su?
- Yes, yes.

21:27.760 --> 21:29.230
I'm here to give you
some good words.

21:29.230 --> 21:32.630
I'm sorry but if you're not going to
buy anything, I need to leave now...

21:32.730 --> 21:35.130
- Do you believe in Jesus?
- I do! I believe in Jesus.

21:35.700 --> 21:40.230
Must be another Jesus.
Believe in our Jesus and go to heaven, sonny.

21:40.570 --> 21:43.510
- Let me pray for you.
- Excuse me...

21:44.340 --> 21:48.180
Our Lord and Savior,
we pray for Lee Hyeon-su.

21:48.550 --> 21:56.250
Hyeon-su's working very, very hard
in this store even on a hot day.

21:56.390 --> 21:59.650
Pour down your grace
upon Hyeon-su, our Lord and Savior...

22:13.140 --> 22:14.130
One, please.

22:15.040 --> 22:16.670
'The One' cigarette?
Which one?

22:17.380 --> 22:19.470
- One.
- You mean 1 mm?

22:19.610 --> 22:21.380
- Esse.
- Esse cigarette?

22:21.380 --> 22:22.750
Which one do you want?

22:23.020 --> 22:25.180
ONE, ESSE.

22:26.850 --> 22:30.150
Either existence or one.
It's a difficult question.

22:30.390 --> 22:31.380
Excuse me?

22:31.490 --> 22:33.790
Do you know the Latin root for Esse?

22:34.260 --> 22:36.400
Sir, if you're not going to buy anything,
I need to get going.

22:36.400 --> 22:39.670
To exist.
Esse One comes to exist as a being.

22:39.670 --> 22:43.030
And by existence here,
it refers to the fundamental One.

22:43.370 --> 22:44.640
So would you like The One?

22:44.640 --> 22:47.410
The ancient philosopher Parmenides said,
"Existence is One.

22:47.410 --> 22:49.710
What exists, exists;
what doesn't, doesn't."

22:49.710 --> 22:54.200
Because thinking exists,
and nothingness does not.

22:54.310 --> 22:57.910
If a burger rots,
is it not a burger anymore?

22:58.050 --> 23:01.190
Does it rot because it's a burger?
Or is it a burger because it rots?

23:01.190 --> 23:05.490
The world of senses is in this producing,
changing world we exist.

23:05.490 --> 23:09.150
In other words, the existence, the essence,
the nature of a burger... Idea is one.

23:09.260 --> 23:12.660
If the existence is all one,
what are humans trying to become one with?

23:12.770 --> 23:14.870
It's the One, the Absolute.

23:14.870 --> 23:17.370
People's desires to identify themselves
with the One can be found everywhere.

23:17.370 --> 23:20.240
Because people think manifestation of
existence relies on the religion.

23:20.240 --> 23:22.370
But... is salvation possible?

23:22.480 --> 23:24.380
Sir, what is it that you want?

23:24.380 --> 23:27.640
To want? What?
What do I exist for?

23:27.910 --> 23:28.980
Raison d'etre?

23:28.980 --> 23:30.580
Raison!
You want 'Raison,' the cigarette?

23:30.580 --> 23:33.090
There's something called the principle
of sufficient reason.

23:33.090 --> 23:34.720
Everything exists for a reason.

23:34.720 --> 23:38.990
You, me, and all of us exist for a reason.
So please.

23:39.290 --> 23:41.320
Don't ever be sorry that
you were born.

23:41.430 --> 23:44.920
We all have the reason for existence
But the problem is our reason.

23:45.030 --> 23:49.330
Because of our reason
we put ourselves in agony.

23:49.440 --> 23:51.170
It's because we separated a priori
from the experience of the body

23:51.170 --> 23:53.440
and thus came to think
we internally have the pure rational concept

23:53.440 --> 23:55.280
as a universal form of experience.
Ergo raison d'etre.

23:55.280 --> 23:58.370
So do you want blue or black?

23:58.480 --> 24:03.050
Neoplatonist Plotinus believed that
there's another world beyond the reason

24:03.050 --> 24:06.090
and that we can return to the absolute,
or become One through that world.

24:06.090 --> 24:09.460
But reason must admit infinity,
so truth is in essential, abominable.

24:09.460 --> 24:12.860
Look.
In the end, the truth id ugly.

24:12.960 --> 24:16.420
"Art exists for humans to not perish
by reason."

24:17.000 --> 24:19.330
That's what Nietzsche said.
Nietzsche.

24:20.170 --> 24:23.190
If Nietzsche came by to buy cigarettes,
he would've said,

24:28.240 --> 24:29.670
One Marlboro, please.

24:30.780 --> 24:32.470
Red or light?

24:32.850 --> 24:35.110
Do you know the Latin root
of the word 'red'?

24:37.750 --> 24:40.120
- It's 2,700 won?
- Yes, it is.

24:40.450 --> 24:45.190
Wait, I've too many coins here...

24:45.730 --> 24:48.350
If you ain't got no money,
then fuck off!

24:49.430 --> 24:52.230
Don't ever be sorry you were born.
It was a pleasure.

25:08.380 --> 25:10.150
Hello?
I'm coming up right now!

25:10.150 --> 25:12.080
<i>No, you don't have to.</i>

25:12.520 --> 25:16.790
You're kidding me.
Please, I prepped so much for this.

25:16.790 --> 25:18.220
So just give me one more shot.

25:18.590 --> 25:20.890
<i>We've given you
as much as we can.</i>

25:20.890 --> 25:22.990
<i>I'm afraid you're not fit for us.</i>

25:24.800 --> 25:25.960
Right...

25:26.230 --> 25:28.900
<i>Don't you think that being on time
is pretty basic?</i>

25:28.900 --> 25:32.070
I'm very sorry.
I guess I'll try out next time...

25:32.070 --> 25:34.130
<i>We've already given you a chance.</i>

25:34.840 --> 25:38.480
<i>You must've prepared a lot, but I'm afraid
I can't do anything for you at this point.</i>

25:38.480 --> 25:40.570
<i>Don't let this disappoint you.
There are a lot of...</i>

