59:33.880 --> 59:36.510
Um, I'm not a customer.
I came to find some part-time work.

59:37.010 --> 59:39.480
<i>You look pretty young.
Aren't you in high school?</i>

59:39.680 --> 59:40.710
No.

59:41.220 --> 59:43.880
- How old are you?
- I'm eight-fuckin-teen.

59:44.260 --> 59:47.750
- Say what?
- Oops! I'm eighteen.

59:48.790 --> 59:50.020
Show me your ID.

59:52.860 --> 59:54.190
Here it is, sir.

59:57.000 --> 59:58.090
Welcome.

01:00:01.310 --> 01:00:02.640
You're a student, alright.

01:00:02.710 --> 01:00:03.970
Nope, I'm not.

01:00:04.480 --> 01:00:06.310
- You don't go to school?
- Nope.

01:00:07.080 --> 01:00:08.840
How come you
don't go to school?

01:00:09.410 --> 01:00:12.870
And what was that about
eight-fuckin-teen, to a grownup.

01:00:12.980 --> 01:00:15.110
Eighteen!
That's how you say it properly.

01:00:15.250 --> 01:00:16.650
Didn't you learn that in school?

01:00:17.050 --> 01:00:18.540
I dropped out.

01:00:19.960 --> 01:00:22.690
Sir, this is 'buy two, get one free'.
You can get another bottle.

01:00:22.690 --> 01:00:24.090
Oh, that so?

01:00:25.600 --> 01:00:29.050
- What do you do if you're not in school?
- I write.

01:00:29.800 --> 01:00:30.820
You write?

01:00:32.170 --> 01:00:36.370
Hey. I'm telling you, kid.
School won't wait for you forever.

01:00:36.370 --> 01:00:38.510
You should be studying
in school at your age!

01:00:38.510 --> 01:00:39.980
You can't earn money
from writing!

01:00:40.410 --> 01:00:41.440
Yes, I can.

01:00:43.580 --> 01:00:46.110
Hey.
You know nothing about life right now.

01:00:46.580 --> 01:00:50.620
And if you're looking for work,
you should be polite, not grinning like that.

01:00:50.620 --> 01:00:52.680
Would you hire yourself
if you were in my position?

01:00:53.790 --> 01:00:56.890
Stop laughing, kid!
Front of a grown-up like me...

01:00:57.030 --> 01:00:59.860
You're not fit for us.
Go somewhere else.

01:01:02.030 --> 01:01:05.000
- Fucking bastard.
- That little...

01:01:05.770 --> 01:01:07.400
That rude son of a bitch.

01:01:12.910 --> 01:01:14.170
That'll be 2,400 won.

01:01:19.080 --> 01:01:22.180
- Please, take this.
- Thank you so much, sir!

01:01:22.290 --> 01:01:24.480
You're so hard-working.

01:01:24.690 --> 01:01:26.490
And you don't even hire
part-time workers...

01:01:26.590 --> 01:01:29.330
Can't trust kids these days,
you know?

01:01:29.330 --> 01:01:31.920
Irresponsible and greedy...

01:01:32.200 --> 01:01:33.530
How's the business going?

01:01:33.960 --> 01:01:35.130
It's alright.

01:01:35.130 --> 01:01:36.860
The economy's really bad
these days, you know.

01:01:37.000 --> 01:01:39.230
I don't get any customers
at all either.

01:01:39.700 --> 01:01:41.690
You own the sashimi place, right?

01:01:41.810 --> 01:01:44.180
Yes. Please come to
my place more often.

01:01:44.180 --> 01:01:45.310
I'll give you a good service.

01:01:45.310 --> 01:01:46.670
Yes.
Thank you very much.

01:01:46.910 --> 01:01:49.040
- Have a good day.
- Same for you.

01:01:49.610 --> 01:01:50.670
Hey.

01:01:50.920 --> 01:01:53.410
We'll get through the hard times.
Cheers!

01:01:53.720 --> 01:01:54.840
Cheers!

01:02:26.380 --> 01:02:29.980
Shit... this is way too heavy...

01:02:36.590 --> 01:02:40.160
- This one is not for sale?
- No.

01:02:49.710 --> 01:02:51.330
Any trouble while I was away?

01:02:51.480 --> 01:02:55.000
Not at all! I've been here all along,
so how can anything happen?

01:03:09.460 --> 01:03:11.020
What the... it doesn't match.

01:03:12.530 --> 01:03:13.830
- Hey.
- Yes, sir.

01:03:13.830 --> 01:03:19.500
- Did you check the inventory for today?
- Yes, I did.

01:03:19.970 --> 01:03:21.530
It doesn't match up, though.

01:03:35.250 --> 01:03:36.220
It's not matching up.

01:03:39.460 --> 01:03:41.080
What's going on here?

01:03:45.660 --> 01:03:46.860
What's this?

01:03:48.070 --> 01:03:51.260
Chips past their expiration date
can be discarded, right?

01:03:53.870 --> 01:03:58.280
No, snacks shouldn't be discarded.

01:03:58.280 --> 01:04:01.040
Think how long this thing's
expiration date is.

01:04:01.480 --> 01:04:05.780
Oh... I ate one
because I thought otherwise...

01:04:06.180 --> 01:04:09.180
- I'll pay for that.
- No, no, that's alright.

01:04:09.390 --> 01:04:14.020
Just don't do it next time.

01:04:16.730 --> 01:04:18.830
And you know, the inventory's
not matching up these days.

01:04:18.830 --> 01:04:21.060
So please check a bit more carefully.

01:04:21.200 --> 01:04:22.270
This stuff is all money.

01:04:22.270 --> 01:04:25.570
If it doesn't match up,
I have to pay the head branch myself.

01:04:26.640 --> 01:04:28.870
Yes, sir.
I understand.

01:04:46.990 --> 01:04:47.660
Hey, mom.

01:04:47.660 --> 01:04:51.560
<i>Mija's mom asked me
when you can pay her back...</i>

01:04:51.660 --> 01:04:54.130
I asked you to wait a bit.

01:04:54.330 --> 01:04:57.200
<i>That's what I'm telling her,
but that woman's keep...</i>

01:04:57.200 --> 01:04:59.870
Mom, mom, mom.
Hang on, hang on.

01:04:59.870 --> 01:05:01.770
<i>I'll get my hands on
money pretty soon.</i>

01:05:01.770 --> 01:05:04.040
<i>Is your business going better?</i>

01:05:04.310 --> 01:05:06.140
How can it?

01:05:06.140 --> 01:05:08.510
After the electricity bills, the rent,
and paying these kids...

01:05:08.510 --> 01:05:10.410
I get nothing for myself.

01:05:10.550 --> 01:05:14.040
And the money I send to
the head branch everyday...

01:05:14.180 --> 01:05:15.590
those bastards.

01:05:15.590 --> 01:05:18.420
<i>Then how are going to
get the money?</i>

01:05:18.420 --> 01:05:21.130
I've something in mind.
Don't worry, just get some rest.

01:05:21.130 --> 01:05:24.190
<i>Don't use part-time workers.
I can help you out.</i>

01:05:24.190 --> 01:05:27.960
Mom, how can you work here.
At your age.

01:05:28.630 --> 01:05:33.500
Customers don't like old people
working here anyways.

01:05:34.610 --> 01:05:35.770
<i>Alright...</i>

01:05:36.210 --> 01:05:38.070
Mom, please get some rest.

01:06:03.370 --> 01:06:04.660
Oh, Lord...

01:06:09.770 --> 01:06:11.540
Sir!
What are you doing here?

01:06:11.840 --> 01:06:15.180
- You're back!
- I wanted to see you again.

01:06:15.880 --> 01:06:20.020
Actually... I came to get more of those
honey water bottles for my workers.

01:06:20.020 --> 01:06:22.210
Sure.
Please bring them here.

01:06:34.500 --> 01:06:38.770
So if I get these
four it'd be 4,800 won, right?

01:06:38.770 --> 01:06:39.900
Two for free.

01:06:39.900 --> 01:06:40.800
Yes.

01:06:41.940 --> 01:06:43.460
Wait, hold on.

01:06:50.950 --> 01:06:53.470
Has this been being selling as
'buy two, get one free'?

01:06:54.250 --> 01:06:56.340
Yes.
Is there any problem?

01:06:56.950 --> 01:07:00.360
Didn't you check the date here?
It says until July.

01:07:01.020 --> 01:07:05.590
If so, then why... the computer said
it was still on sale.

01:07:05.730 --> 01:07:07.970
How many times did I tell you,

01:07:07.970 --> 01:07:12.330
the head branch workers make mistakes
so you need to be more careful!

01:07:17.940 --> 01:07:21.100
We're sorry.
That'll be 7,200 won.

01:07:21.950 --> 01:07:27.140
Wait, he told me it was 'buy two, get one free'
just a while ago... and I got one free.

01:07:27.620 --> 01:07:29.920
- You did?
- Yes.

01:07:32.490 --> 01:07:34.180
No... Sir, I apologize.

01:07:34.290 --> 01:07:39.750
But it's no longer on sale.
So you have to pay 7,200 won.

01:07:40.900 --> 01:07:43.330
That's none of my business.

01:07:43.430 --> 01:07:46.800
If the sale policy's changed without an
announcement to customers,

01:07:46.800 --> 01:07:49.040
it should be sold the way
customers know it.

01:07:49.040 --> 01:07:50.610
It's not like you've
opened business recently.

01:07:50.610 --> 01:07:53.840
I run business too.
This isn't how you should work.

01:07:59.080 --> 01:08:03.150
OK. I apologize, sir.
Just give it to him.

01:08:03.150 --> 01:08:04.480
'Buy two, get one... '

01:08:08.090 --> 01:08:09.860
Sir, please take these...

01:08:09.860 --> 01:08:12.730
I'm not buying anymore!
Go drink these up yourself!

01:08:12.730 --> 01:08:15.200
Are you kidding with me?

01:08:15.200 --> 01:08:17.130
For a couple bucks.
Jesus.

01:08:43.859 --> 01:08:46.090
Dammit. Shit...

01:09:01.010 --> 01:09:03.979
You think chips can be discarded?
You think?!

01:10:22.330 --> 01:10:27.190
<i>Interview results.
Please press your interview ID.</i>

01:10:34.740 --> 01:10:38.700
<i>The following is
the report for 0505033.</i>

01:10:39.280 --> 01:10:42.410
<i>We regret to inform you that we
cannot offer the position at this time.</i>

01:10:42.410 --> 01:10:44.540
<i>Thank you for applying.</i>

01:10:44.950 --> 01:10:48.850
<i>If you'd like to hear it again,
please press 1.</i>

01:10:49.190 --> 01:10:51.050
<i>If you'd like to return...</i>

01:11:06.140 --> 01:11:08.260
That'll be 3,650 won.

01:11:10.140 --> 01:11:12.200
How much is this?

01:11:14.110 --> 01:11:15.610
This one's 800 won.

01:11:15.610 --> 01:11:19.070
It's on a 'buy one, get one free' sale,
so you can go get one more.

01:11:19.180 --> 01:11:21.170
What about this and this?

01:11:21.350 --> 01:11:25.090
This is 850 won,
and this is 1,000 won.

01:11:25.090 --> 01:11:29.460
I'll just get these.
So much more expensive than mine.

01:11:29.630 --> 01:11:33.960
They're from yesterday, too...
I'll get this too.

01:11:37.270 --> 01:11:38.930
That'll be 1,600 won.

01:11:52.480 --> 01:11:56.280
<i>No worries,
everybody say, TEA CHA CHA</i>

01:11:56.550 --> 01:12:00.250
Si-hu!
You've eaten yet?

01:12:01.360 --> 01:12:04.350
I'm about to eat now.

01:12:05.530 --> 01:12:10.520
A lot of yummy rice
and side-dishes today.

01:12:12.770 --> 01:12:16.030
I'm feeling really good today.

01:12:16.370 --> 01:12:17.810
Alright.

01:12:20.510 --> 01:12:23.100
I love you, son.

01:12:28.690 --> 01:12:31.480
Ouch!
Hot, hot!

01:12:31.760 --> 01:12:35.660
Yikes!
So hot.

01:12:41.300 --> 01:12:43.270
<i>How may I help you?</i>

01:12:44.600 --> 01:12:46.500
Nonghyup Bank.

01:12:46.840 --> 01:12:49.170
<i>That's a difficult question to answer.</i>

01:12:50.470 --> 01:12:52.500
Nong-hyup-ban-k.

01:12:53.280 --> 01:12:55.400
<i>That's a difficult question.</i>

01:12:56.510 --> 01:12:58.220
Nong-hyup-ban-k.

01:12:58.220 --> 01:13:00.240
<i>Please press your account password.</i>

01:13:02.450 --> 01:13:07.010
<i>Your current account balance
is 35,479 won.</i>

01:13:07.320 --> 01:13:10.120
<i>To hear this message again,
please press 1, to return...</i>

01:13:20.840 --> 01:13:25.500
Convenience stores don't
even get off on holidays.

01:13:25.780 --> 01:13:28.070
There's no day off
at convenience stores.

01:13:28.450 --> 01:13:31.880
Well, props to you for being
here instead of hanging out

01:13:31.880 --> 01:13:35.850
with your boyfriend and friends
on such a nice weather like this.

01:13:35.850 --> 01:13:38.760
I'm not a kid anymore, you know.
I need to make my ends meet.

01:13:38.760 --> 01:13:43.520
You're such
a hardworking young lady.

01:13:47.430 --> 01:13:49.300
May fortune smile on you.

01:13:50.930 --> 01:13:52.560
It's for me?

01:13:56.840 --> 01:13:58.740
Oh gosh,
what did I just do!

01:13:58.740 --> 01:14:02.770
I was supposed to give you
this first, not that.

01:14:02.910 --> 01:14:05.070
I'm losing my mind.

01:14:05.750 --> 01:14:06.950
That'll be 1,400 won.

01:14:06.950 --> 01:14:09.010
- Did I surprise you?
- No, it's alright.

01:14:14.090 --> 01:14:15.820
Here's your change.

01:14:20.600 --> 01:14:23.900
- You have toilet paper here?
- It's up there.

01:14:24.070 --> 01:14:25.500
- Over there?
- Yes.

01:14:29.270 --> 01:14:30.260
How much is it?

01:14:33.340 --> 01:14:35.440
That'll be 15,600 won.

01:14:35.750 --> 01:14:39.480
Why's it so expensive? It's so much
more expensive than where I live.

01:14:41.150 --> 01:14:43.280
What are you doing?

01:14:43.520 --> 01:14:46.390
- Are you going to buy it?
- I guess I've no choice.

01:14:47.820 --> 01:14:51.350
20,000 won received.
Would you like the receipt?

01:14:57.100 --> 01:15:00.830
- Hurry up.
- Here's 4,400 won, your change.

01:15:00.970 --> 01:15:05.040
- Where's my receipt?
- You just said you didn't need it.

01:15:05.040 --> 01:15:06.600
When?

01:15:06.740 --> 01:15:10.180
Do I have to tell you these things?
That's such a basic thing!

01:15:10.310 --> 01:15:13.210
And by the way,
what's with the attitude?

01:15:13.920 --> 01:15:18.190
- Then I'll get it for you.
- No, you're not doing me a favor.

01:15:18.190 --> 01:15:20.050
It's my right.

01:15:20.220 --> 01:15:23.590
- What's your number?
- 011-9939-0348

01:15:24.030 --> 01:15:25.520
It's all done.

01:15:25.630 --> 01:15:28.890
- Where's the restroom here?
- We don't have one.

01:15:29.130 --> 01:15:30.100
Why not?

01:15:30.330 --> 01:15:32.490
There's no restrooms
in convenient stores, usually.

01:15:32.670 --> 01:15:36.970
That makes no sense.
There must be a restroom that you use.

01:15:36.970 --> 01:15:38.980
If you don't want to tell me,
then say it.

01:15:38.980 --> 01:15:40.980
Don't lie to me when it's obvious.

01:15:40.980 --> 01:15:42.880
Do you shit here then?
Right here?

01:15:42.880 --> 01:15:46.010
Then try shitting here!
Go ahead!

01:15:46.280 --> 01:15:50.020
Outsiders are not allowed in our restroom.
Don't talk to me like that.

01:15:50.020 --> 01:15:52.490
Let's get this straight,
I'm a customer here.

01:15:52.490 --> 01:15:56.190
What's with the service here?
I really got to go.

01:15:56.860 --> 01:15:59.830
Hey, lady!
There's really no restroom here?

01:16:00.030 --> 01:16:01.360
I'm not sure.

01:16:02.470 --> 01:16:05.990
Whatever, fine!
I'm returning this.

01:16:06.100 --> 01:16:08.200
I was getting this
because of the restroom.

01:16:09.010 --> 01:16:11.370
- OK, ma'am.
- This is killing me.

01:16:15.510 --> 01:16:20.180
- What's wrong with this?
- It's killing me...

01:16:20.320 --> 01:16:21.650
I'm sorry.
Hold on, please.

01:16:21.650 --> 01:16:25.020
You're doing this on purpose
right now?

01:16:25.390 --> 01:16:26.950
Hurry up, please.

01:16:27.220 --> 01:16:31.660
I'll be back in a minute,
so have the refund ready.

01:16:40.200 --> 01:16:41.400
Welcome.

01:16:41.970 --> 01:16:45.200
<i>Work's pretty tough, isn't it?
You seem pretty frustrated.</i>

01:16:45.940 --> 01:16:47.070
No.

01:16:47.940 --> 01:16:49.430
This is empty.

01:16:49.880 --> 01:16:52.870
There weren't any gimbap on the rack either.
You guys aren't selling it?

01:16:53.180 --> 01:16:54.980
The stock isn't in yet.

01:16:55.120 --> 01:16:57.280
So the owner
didn't order them yet?

01:16:57.390 --> 01:17:01.220
He did, but he does it a bit late.
We're sorry.

01:17:01.220 --> 01:17:03.560
The management here
seems a little iffy here.

01:17:05.900 --> 01:17:08.090
Do you need something?

01:17:12.740 --> 01:17:14.000
Welcome.

01:17:40.830 --> 01:17:42.420
How've you been?

01:17:45.600 --> 01:17:47.260
Thank you for coming.

01:17:53.740 --> 01:17:55.210
He wasn't a customer, right?

01:17:55.310 --> 01:17:59.180
He is... sort of,
but not really.

01:17:59.550 --> 01:18:00.610
Then who was that?

01:18:00.720 --> 01:18:03.650
He comes to drink that soju
he keeps here.

01:18:06.490 --> 01:18:10.620
Wait... you let people
keep soju here?

01:18:11.430 --> 01:18:15.900
It's just... he doesn't want to
finish it all at once, that's why...

01:18:15.900 --> 01:18:17.590
You think this is funny?

01:18:19.500 --> 01:18:20.730
I'm sorry.

01:18:20.970 --> 01:18:23.710
Does the manager here know
that the beggar comes by?

01:18:23.710 --> 01:18:25.470
The manager said it's fine.

01:18:26.540 --> 01:18:27.700
He did?

01:18:31.280 --> 01:18:34.840
Wow... this really is something...

01:18:39.990 --> 01:18:42.460
Hello? Are you owner
of the Seori branch?

01:18:42.830 --> 01:18:44.690
Yes, I'm from the head branch.

01:18:46.160 --> 01:18:50.300
It seems messy here.
The stock's not organized,

01:18:50.300 --> 01:18:54.240
the part-time worker's
not nice to customers...

01:18:54.740 --> 01:18:56.970
And strange bums
coming into the store...

01:18:57.710 --> 01:18:59.680
I'm giving you a warning.

01:19:01.310 --> 01:19:05.850
I see that you've closed night shifts
a few times too without permission.

01:19:05.850 --> 01:19:10.510
And there's even repeated reports of
not paying for workers.

01:19:13.290 --> 01:19:16.350
You know this might lead to
a cancellation of the contract, right?

01:19:17.430 --> 01:19:18.890
We'll be watching.

01:19:26.540 --> 01:19:32.070
If not for that scar...
I wonder what the customers will think.

01:19:36.650 --> 01:19:37.870
Take care.

01:19:49.330 --> 01:19:50.090
Yes, Mr. Chun.

01:19:50.090 --> 01:19:54.860
<i>Why is it that the head
branch just called me?</i>

01:19:55.400 --> 01:19:57.470
<i>- No, it's...
- I heard enough.</i>

01:19:57.470 --> 01:19:58.900
<i>Just close the shop and get out.</i>

01:19:58.900 --> 01:20:03.570
<i>You think I hired you to mess around
at work and give you every penny?</i>

01:20:03.940 --> 01:20:06.710
It's not like you've seen
the whole thing.

01:20:06.710 --> 01:20:08.410
You've only listened to
one side of the story.

01:20:08.410 --> 01:20:12.680
<i>I just got a call from the head branch,
so isn't it pretty obvious?!</i>

01:20:12.780 --> 01:20:15.620
<i>I can't work with kids like you,
so get out of there right now.</i>

01:20:15.720 --> 01:20:19.520
Sounds good. It's not like
I'm going to work here forever.

01:20:19.520 --> 01:20:21.790
<i>You're fired, so close the store
and get the hell out!</i>

01:20:21.790 --> 01:20:23.730
<i>- Mr. Chun.
- What?</i>

01:20:23.860 --> 01:20:28.530
If you backstab someone who's worked
this hard then no one can work with you!

01:20:28.530 --> 01:20:30.190
<i>What is this crap!</i>

01:20:34.670 --> 01:20:37.540
<i>1002-3472-0572365.
Nonghyup Bank. Kim Min-hee.</i>

01:21:05.170 --> 01:21:07.070
Is something wrong?

01:21:09.370 --> 01:21:10.930
I just got fired.

01:21:11.270 --> 01:21:16.180
Oh no, on such a nice day...

01:21:20.350 --> 01:21:22.440
I'll just look for another job,
I guess.

01:21:22.750 --> 01:21:24.520
What about the store here?

01:21:24.820 --> 01:21:27.310
He told me to shut it
and get the hell out.

01:21:29.030 --> 01:21:33.890
What in the world...

